Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C. Halve, then remove the cores from the @red pepper{1} and @yellow pepper{1} and chop into 2cm chunks. Place the peppers on a #baking tray{} and drizzle over a splash of @oil{}. Roast on the top shelf of your oven until slightly crispy at the edges, ~{15%minutes}.

Boil the @water{275%ml} in a large #saucepan{} and add the @vegetable stock pot{½}. Stir to dissolve then add the @buckwheat{2%cups}. Bring back to the boil then pop on a lid. Cook on medium heat for ~{10%minutes}, then remove and set aside with the lid still on (don't peek until it's time to serve!).

Halve, peel and finely chop the @red onion{½}. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve the @green chilli{½} lengthways, remove the seeds and finely chop. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}. Roughly chop the @chives{½} or snip them with a pair of #scissors{}. Drain and rinse the @black beans{1} in a #colander{}.

Heat a splash of @olive oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Add the onion and cook until softened, ~{5%minutes}. Add the garlic, chilli, @cumin{½%tsp}, @mild paprika{½%tsp} and @ground cinnamon{½%tsp}. Cook for ~{1%minute} more. Add the black beans and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Cook for ~{1%minute} more then remove from the heat.

> TIP: Some like it hot but if you don't, just add less chilli!

Once the buckwheat is done (it should be dry not soggy), fluff it up with a #fork{} to separate the grains. Combine with your black bean mixture. Add the roasted peppers and stir through half the @crème fraîche{1}. Test for seasoning and add more salt or black pepper if necessary.

Tip the buckwheat and black bean mixture into an #ovenproof dish{} and top with the cheese. Place on the top shelf of your oven. Bake until the top is beautifully golden and crisp, about ~{10%minutes}. Serve with a big dollop of crème fraîche and a scattering of chives. Enjoy!